A reaction officer in Durban was shot multiple times while on patrol inside his company car on Wednesday night. The shooting took place on Lyttleton Avenue in Reservoir Hills and the officer is believed to have been shot in the stomach and legs. Garrith Jamieson, ALS Paramedics spokesperson, said the officer who is believed to be in his forties was stabilised on the scene and taken to a nearby hospital for further treatment. He remains in a critical condition, said Jamieson. According to a statement by Inkosi Security Services, the officer was attacked by six unknown gunmen travelling with two vehicles (silver Mercedes hatchback and white unknown vehicle) with an unknown registration number. “This vehicle (Mercedes) is believed to be the same vehicle used at Nola Terrace shooting on the 6th June where the Inkosi response officers was also shot at,” said Inkosi in a statement.